Sokoto – Governor Aminu Waziri Tambuwal of Sokoto State has dissolved his executive council with immediate effect. The sacked commissioners are to hand over the affairs of their respective ministries to the permanent secretaries. The dissolution according to his newly appointed Director-General, Media and Public Affairs, Malam Abubakar Shekara, is aimed at restructuring and restrategising the cabinet for optimum efficiency as well as service delivery to the state. The governor thanked members of the council for their dedication, sacrifice and loyalty to his administration. While expressing his appreciation to them for their co-operation, governor Tambuwal wished the outgoing executive council members success in their future endeavours. comments Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE. 